Aedeagus: Length 0.30 mm .; mainpiece slightly sinuate, apex symmetrical, wedgeshaped; distal part of internal tube suboval to oval; parameres with longer seta of distal pair very long, three times as long as shorter seta, curving (
Fig. 10
).

Distribution. Currently known from the Australian Capital Territory, New South Wales , and Victoria (
Fig. 18
).
